Name: Luxembourg 10-year Government Bond Yield
Periodicity:
Annual From Dec 1946 To Dec 1969
Monthly From Jan 1970 To Oct 1993
Daily From Oct 1993 To Mar 2023
Monthly From Mar 2023 To May 2025
Metadata: Sources: Annuaire Statistique de Luxembourg (1946-1969), Institut Monetaire Luxembourgeois, Bulletin Trimestriel (1970-)  Notes: Data are annual through 1969 and monthly thereafter. Due to the fact that the Luxembourg Government does not have outstanding long-term debt securities with a residual maturity of close to ten years, the indicator is based on a basket of long-term bonds. This basket has an average residual maturity of close to ten years. The bonds are issued by a private credit institution and the indicator is thus not fully harmonised.  Luxembourg issued a 10-year bond in 1998, but its maturity has declined and the daily data for the bond are currently found in the 5-year series. Source: Eurostat. Eurostat collects data from the statistical agencies of the 27 member countries of the European Economic Community, candidate countries (Macedonia, Croatia and Turkey), EFTA countries (Iceland, Norway, Liechtenstein and Switzerland) as well as other countries (Japan, Australia, United States). Statistical agencies within each country disseminate their national data to Eurostat in order that it can be made available in a consistent format.
